ias":"science.math.Optimization.Linear Programming"},{"from":{"fname":"science.math.Optimization.Convex Optimization","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1,"offset":123},"end":{"line":5,"column":49,"offset":171},"indent":[]},"value":"science.math.Optimization.Linear Programming","alias":"science.math.Optimization.Linear Programming"},{"from":{"fname":"science.math.modelling.Operations Research","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":87},"end":{"line":4,"column":49,"offset":135},"indent":[]},"value":"science.math.Optimization.Linear Programming","alias":"science.math.Optimization.Linear Programming"},{"from":{"fname":"science.stats.Regression.Linear Regression","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1,"offset":435},"end":{"line":25,"column":49,"offset":483},"indent":[]},"value":"science.math.Optimization.Linear Programming","alias":"science.math.Optimization.Linear Programming"},{"from":{"fname":"science.math.Optimization.Convex Optimization.Duality","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1,"offset":662},"end":{"line":25,"column":49,"offset":710},"indent":[]},"value":"science.math.Optimization.Linear Programming","alias":"science.math.Optimization.Linear Programming"},{"from":{"fname":"science.math.Optimization.Convex Optimization.Duality","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":3,"offset":798},"end":{"line":30,"column":60,"offset":855},"indent":[]},"value":"science.math.Optimization.Linear Programming","alias":"science.math.Optimization.Linear Programming"},{"from":{"fname":"science.math.Optimization.Linear Programming.Stochastic Programming.Benders Decomposition","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":56},"end":{"line":4,"column":49,"offset":104},"indent":[]},"value":"science.math.Optimization.Linear Programming","alias":"science.math.Optimization.Linear Programming"}],"anchors":{"resources":{"type":"header","text":"Resources","value":"resources","line":16,"column":0,"depth":1},"duality":{"type":"header","text":"Duality","value":"duality","line":23,"column":0,"depth":1}},"children":["jsk6BZ3ldCY2CNXf78w6D"],"parent":"4FIxH4rGwMUvVyCogNmHe","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"linear-programming\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#linear-programming\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Linear Programming</h1>\n<p><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/LW3beEZT5jbJ2BHBOqwR9\">Simplex</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/V850K8TkKzlMQiS3afp14\">JuMP</a></p>\n<h1 id=\"resources\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#resources\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Resources</h1>\n<p><a title=\"Private\" style=\"color: brown\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\">#lowprio (Private)</a>\n<a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B-C_0LZtyGcNaVluTjBvZDlNUGc&#x26;resourcekey=0-d9atqT3fimtNzM9F_9fhOQ&#x26;authuser=stefanvpetrov%40gmail.com&#x26;usp=drive_fs\">Some Matlab LP book link</a>.</p>\n<h1 id=\"duality\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#duality\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Duality</h1>\n<p>Suppose we have the following linear program in a\ncannonical form:</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>minimize </mtext><mi>c</mi><mo>⋅</mo><mi>x</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mtext>subject to </mtext><mi>A</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>b</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mi>x</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\text{minimize } c\\cdot x \\\\ \\text{subject to } Ax \\leq b,\\\\ x \\geq 0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6679em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">minimize </span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">⋅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span></span><span class=\"mspace newline\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">subject to </span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≤</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">b</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span></span><span class=\"mspace newline\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7719em;vertical-align:-0.136em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≥</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span></span></div>\n<p>Then, let's define the following polytope in the variables <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span></span></span></span></span>:</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>A</mi><mi>T</mi></msup><mi>y</mi><mo>≥</mo><mi>c</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mi>y</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A^T y \\geq c\\\\ y \\geq 0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0858em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8913em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≥</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span></span><span class=\"mspace newline\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8304em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≥</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span></span></div>\n<p>Then, left-multipying both sides of the primal polytope by the <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>y</mi><mi>T</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">y^T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0358em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, we get:</p>\n<p><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>y</mi><mi>T</mi></msup><mi>b</mi><mo>≥</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mi>T</mi></msup><mi>A</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>≥</mo><msup><mi>c</mi><mi>T</mi></msup><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">y^T b\\geq y^T A x\\geq c^Tx</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0358em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">b</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≥</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0358em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≥</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>Thus, <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>y</mi><mi>T</mi></msup><mi>b</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">y^T b</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0358em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">b</span></span></span></span></span> is an upper bound for <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>c</mi><mi>T</mi></msup><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">c^T x</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span></span></span></span></span>, and if we consider the following dual program:</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>min </mtext><msup><mi>y</mi><mi>T</mi></msup><mi>b</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><msup><mi>A</mi><mi>T</mi></msup><mi>y</mi><mo>≥</mo><mi>c</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mi>y</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\text{min } y^T b \\\\ A^T y \\geq c\\\\ y \\geq 0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0858em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">min </span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8913em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">b</span></span><span class=\"mspace newline\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0858em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8913em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≥</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span></span><span class=\"mspace newline\"></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8304em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≥</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span></span></div>\n<p>We get the smallest upper bounds...</p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Children</strong>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/jsk6BZ3ldCY2CNXf78w6D\">Stochastic Programming</a></li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/4FIxH4rGwMUvVyCogNmHe\">Optimization</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/W5KwHEIyMAUXkjZR2PdlA\">Network Flows</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/WPtQ6p4KjbTwf5lGKgfJN\">Convex Optimization</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/vaKM8wgcu4zmD3FODnuWI\">Operations Research</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/YSgeu1I7ZeKOAKUbvuL8M\">Linear Regression</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/17wPJ84v4MoKBWHDLZsgf\">Duality</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/F2B3T4vSlYcAz9Xb4ufyz\">Benders Decomposition</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"wn8PE1RhG0znK1alrGFYv","title":"Root","desc":"","up